Rating: 2
I was somewhat disappointed in this recipe, but I want to emphasize that it wasn't the soba noodles (my first go at them) which were every bit as tasty as any other noodle. I plan to use them again in other recipes. I think the salad needed more ingredients, such as the cucumber one reviewer added. I did cut back on the salt as suggested, and added about a teaspoon of minced ginger to the dressing. My dining companion thought the noodles were quite good, thus the 2 fork rating, while I would have rated it 1 fork, or so-so. We both thought the dressing contained too much vinegar, and I felt the salad was overly sweet, perhaps due to the mint. I think that the Sesame Soba Noodle and Vegetable Salad on this site might be more interesting. Heck, maybe I just ate too many cookies before dinner.

